<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/303000091/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """The primary goal of the evaluation is to verify students' ability to implement the methods taught in class. This includes programming the algorithms (directly or using libraries) and applying them to real-world or realistic datasets.

Evaluation components:
In-class evaluation: to encourage active participation rather than passive note-taking
Continuous evaluation: based on 4-5 short assessments throughout the semester to keep students up-to-date
Project evaluations: based on applications in scientific or engineering contexts, emphasizing practical application of classroom concepts

Each project will also involve a 5-10 minute in-class presentation, assessing both presentation skills and understanding. Participation in classmates' presentations will also be evaluated.
Weighting of Evaluation Components:
Attendance and participation: 10%
Assessable assignments, practicals, and individual projects: 40%
Theory exams: 30%
Team project evaluation: 20%

Extraordinary evaluation will also involve:
An assignment, practical, and/or individual projects proposed during the course: 40%
A team project evaluation: 20%
A Theory exam: 40%"""@es ;
